                        "AcquisitionStrategy": {
                            "val": "The NRE will encompass subsystem integration and will utilize existing test aircraft, incorporate the technical insertions, and initiate appropriate qualification and operational flight-testing. \n\nIn FY14, a contract for Apache AH-64E Lot 3, initiating Full Rate Production, was awarded with options for Lot 4.\n\nTraining device concurrency will be maintained with each technical insertion. The Engineering\/Manufacturing Design (EMD) effort is managed as Cost Reimbursable.  Production efforts will be awarded as Fixed Price Incentive (FPI) and include the Advance Procurement requirements.\n\nIn FY13, FY14, and FY15 MRL NRE encompassed US Government (USG) design of the Hydra Launcher Electronics Assembly (LEA), modification of the M261 launcher, launcher fabrication, and launcher testing.\n\nIn FY15-FY19, Apache AH-64E Version 6 System Development and Demonstration (SDD) Contract. \n\nMulti-year production awarded March 15, 2017."
                        },
